<item>
            <title>[FLINK-5330] Harden KafkaConsumer08Test</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5330</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;KafkaConsumer08Test&lt;/tt&gt; assumes that some of the Kafka bootstrap server hostname cannot be resolved. This can lead to failures if these names are wrongly resolved by chance (e.g. if using Google&apos;s DNS server). Moreover, the test cases take a long time to finish because the connection timeouts are set to a high value. This can be decreased to speed these test cases up.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
